name: GoR_2
strategy: I started with modestly low guesses, as those seemed to be more likely to be close to correct. The initial instructions mentioned examples that were relatively low, so I thought other people would be most likely to be primed by those numbers, and I guessed a bit lower to undershoot it. I stuck with this approach when it turned out that the averages tended to be comparable. At the end people were guessing quite low, apparently, but I gambled on the same strategy working anyway -- I'd have needed to be more than twice as certain in numbers such as 10-12 than ones such as 20-25, because of the lower bonus payout associated, and I wasn't that certain.It didn't work out but I have no regrets, since I missed out on just 35 or so cents if I were right all three of the last times, in comparison to the 40+ that even two correct guesses out of three would have yielded.     Anyway, fun game, glad to participate. I'd be interested in being emailed similar studies in the future. :)

Wasn't sure what would happen next, so I went up to meet him (or her) because I thought if we could land on the same number, maybe we'd both get paid, but I lost. I didn't think he would think that I would go down so drastically, so I did just that. But I knew I also wasn't getting a high amount of money. I went a little higher to see if I could still win, but I could see that the bonus amounts were getting progressively lower. I probably should have just kept going down, but that seemed a little defeatest. And then for the last one, I picked a low number that was also my favorite number.
